Solution_Comment__c:
T2 provided the explanation to the customer about the raised questions
1. Uninstall Attempt - when the normal uninstall method was used (remove-epp.sh, uninstall script)
2. Forced Uninstall Attempt - this may occur if someone tries to manipulate the registry, delete files, or terminate the agent.
3. Unplanned Client Termination - this is sent when the EPP service on the endpoint is killed using methods other than the normal one. (ex. a service stop)
4. DPI Bypassed Traffic - When a certain process/service is bypassed by the Bypass functions enabled in the DPI Configuration section. (ex. a website that uses websockets)
5. External Repository Upload Fail - when the file shadows failed to be uploaded to the configured file repository.
